Security agents in Kericho county were on Saturday ordered to arrest inciters.County commissioner Muktar Abdi said politicians engaging in hate speech will be charged. He spoke after a peace caravan which started from Kericho Teachers Training College and ended at Moi Gardens.Abdi told security officials not to fear arresting candidates or other politicians found inciting people to cause chaos.During Jubilee Party nominations, losers complained the results did not reflect the will of voters. Many will run as independents. They include Belgut MP Eric Keter, his Buret and Kipkelion counterparts Leonard Sang and Jackson Rop respectively. Ainamoi MP Benjamin Lang&rsquo;at who had declared his interest in the governor seat, lost during the nominations to incumbent Paul Chepkwony. He will seek to defend his seat as an independent.